The Bush administration has decided to seek $11 billion over two years to protect the nation against bioterrorism, far more than experts had expected.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/04/politics/04CAMP.html?todaysheadlines">In New Hampshire, a New Face Gets a Warm Welcome</a></b><br>
This weekend Senator John Edwards began early presidential politicking in New Hampshire, garnering interest for being a fresh face among the current field of Democrats.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/04/business/04AUDI.html?todaysheadlines">Former Fed Chief Picked to Oversee Auditor of Enron</a></b><br>
