<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>SPORTS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/04/sports/football/04SUPE.html?todaysheadlines">Patriots Claim the Super Bowl</a></b><br>
Adam Vinatieri kicked a 48-yard field goal as time expired to lift the New England Patriots to an improbable win over the St. Louis Rams.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/04/sports/football/04PATS.html?todaysheadlines">Patriots Help Vinatieri Experience the Moment</a></b><br>
Tom Brady's late completions to Troy Brown for 23 yards and Jermaine Wiggins for 6 yards put Adam Vinatieri in his comfort zone.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/04/sports/golf/04GOLF.html?todaysheadlines">Gogel Finds Redemption</a></b><br>
Matt Gogel caught Pat Perez on the back nine and won the AT&amp;T Pebble Beach National Pro-Am for his first PGA Tour victory.
<P>
</font>













