<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>NY REGION</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/04/nyregion/04GOV.html?todaysheadlines">Candidates Try to Fathom New York's Shifting Voters</a></b><br>
The rules that have long guided candidates seeking statewide office in New York seem to have been thrown out the window over the last four years.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/04/nyregion/04STRE.html?todaysheadlines">A Little Violence and Lots of Police Equal 150 Arrests Far From Forum</a></b><br>
The calm that had infused the weekend's protests against the World Economic Forum ended on Sunday, when demonstrators took over parts of the East Village and the Upper East Side.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/04/nyregion/04WOME.html?todaysheadlines">Albany Bill Would Cover Birth Control</a></b><br>
